"Chalo queues ke baare mein samajhte hain. Imagine karo ki aap ek line mein khade ho; line mein enter karna ko hum enqueuing kehte hain, aur har naya person last mein khada hota hai. Jab kisi ko line se nikalte hain, use dequeuing kehte hain. Yeh FIFO basis pe kaam karta hai—First In, First Out. Let’s enqueue kuch aur logon ko, aur phir unhe dequeue karenge.

**A1: Choosing the Right Data Structure for a Queue**

Queue ke liye sahi data structure choose karte time pehle array ke baare mein sochte hain. Yaad rakho, array ke end se push karna ya pop karna O(1) operation hai. Lekin, beginning se add ya remove karna, matlab shift ya unshift karna, O(n) kharch karta hai. Queue mein aap ek end se add karte ho aur dusre se remove karte ho. Operations tab tak efficient hain jab tak ye opposite ends pe ho rahe hain.

Array use karte hue, aap back se enqueue kar sakte ho, jo ki O(n) operation hai, aur front se dequeue, jo ki O(1) operation hai, ya iske ulta bhi kar sakte hain. Kisi bhi situation mein, ek operation hamesha O(n) hoga.

**A2: The Efficiency of Linked Lists**

Ab isko linked list se compare karte hain. End se pop karna O(n) hai, lekin push karna O(1) hai. Iske vipreet, front se shift karna (remove karna) aur unshift karna (add karna) dono O(1) operations hain. Isliye, linked list ka use karke queue banane ke liye best setup yeh hai ki back se enqueue karo aur front se dequeue karo, dono operations O(1) mein ho jaate hain. Jab hum queue ke baare mein baat karte hain to linked list ke ends ko 'first' aur 'last' kehte hain.

